OL,3,CCoventry's U-turn on budget cuts but
OL,4,Ccouncil tax still set to rise
OL,6,FCharities that would have been
OL,7,Faffected by the proposed cuts can
OL,8,Fcontinue to run as normal, without
OL,9,Fworrying about a lack of funding.
OL,11,FFor example, Grapevine, a charity
OL,12,Fwhich supports people with learning
OL,13,Fdisabilities, has had their 45% budget
OL,14,Fcut cancelled, meaning that 750,000
OL,15,Fservice users can continue to get
OL,16,Fsupport.
OL,18,FHow much does the council want to save?
