OL,3,CCoventry's U-turn on budget cuts but
OL,4,Ccouncil tax still set to rise
OL,6,FThis current year (2024-2025) Coventry
OL,7,FCity Council is working towards saving
OL,8,F#30 million, but they have predicted a
OL,9,Fbudget gap of #14 million by next year
OL,10,F(2025/2026).
OL,12,FThe situation improved slightly by the
OL,13,Ftime they went out to a consultation,
OL,14,Fand they found out they had #10.8
OL,15,Fmillion in savings.
OL,17,FDue to a "larger than predicted"
OL,18,Fgovernment settlement for the coming
OL,19,Fyear, they are #2.8 million better off
OL,20,Fbut there is still a budget gap of #8
OL,21,Fmillion.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G3/5
