OL,3,CCoventry's U-turn on budget cuts but
OL,4,Ccouncil tax still set to rise
OL,6,FThey are still predicting the budget
OL,7,Fgap will widen again, with a shortfall
OL,8,Fof #10.5 million by 2028.
OL,10,FWhat does this mean for the public?
OL,12,FCoventry residents will still have to
OL,13,Fpay more council tax, as it increases
OL,14,Fby 4.9% to shorten the budget gap.
OL,16,FIf the budget gap increases further
OL,17,Fthen taxes will rise more, or the
OL,18,Fcouncil will have to go back to their
OL,19,Foriginal plan of making cuts to their
OL,20,Fpublic services, before the government
OL,21,Fintervenes.
